item.description:
The main objective of this project is to predict the value of homes in the city of Boston, in the United States of America. It is a classic regression problem that can be divided into parts:
  Data collection;
  Data division;
  Data pre-processing;
  Exploratory analysis;
  Training of the predictive algorithm;
  Improvement of the predictive algorithm;
  Testing the predictive algorithm.

The present work aims to predict what is known as particulate matter. These particles, more precisely the PM 2.5 are very fine and can be found in fog or smoke, that is to say that the more of these particles appear, the more polluted is local.
The work can be divided into 7 parts:
  Data collect;
  Data division;
  Data pre-processing;
  Exploratory analysis;
